@Lou Scheffer 
Eh, in principle, I suppose. But Michelle YEOH has been so well-known internationally for decades, acting in works of various genres in both film and TV, that her name should be a gimme for most solvers (except maybe those playing the archives decades from now), and even if you can’t remember how to spell her surname, I can’t think of any other plausible letter other than ‘H’ to complete C_AD for the first name of someone whose middle and surnames are “Michael” and “Murray,” respectively. In fact, I’ve never heard of the latter performer, but I happened to fill in the ‘H’ with the down clue using that exact reasoning, even though I would have known for certain from the across.

I actually think this an example of good puzzle construction, precisely because you can rely on your general knowledge of phonology, spelling, and reasonably common names without having to know the trivia.

